# Phase 1: Master Product Catalog Engine

**Priority:** CRITICAL — Foundation for all subsequent phases
**Stack:** Next.js 14 App Router · Prisma · PostgreSQL (Supabase) · TypeScript
**Dev Server:** `npm run dev` — runs at **http://localhost:5000**
**Deployment:** Vercel (serverless) — see `VERCEL_DEPLOYMENT_PLAN.md`

> **Current State:** Core schema, admin CRUD, scraper config UI, and the data pipeline are built. The scraper architecture has been refactored for Vercel serverless deployment — Puppeteer/BullMQ/Redis removed, replaced with external worker dispatch + DB-backed job queue + Supabase Storage image pipeline.

---

## Plan 1-A: Database & Admin Foundation ✅ COMPLETE
*Target: Finalize the data model and build full CRUD admin UI*

### What's Done
- `schema.prisma` defines all core models: `Manufacturer`, `Brand`, `Product`, `ProductImage`, `ProductDocument`, `ProductSpec`, `ProductCategory`, `ProductAttribute`, `ManufacturerIntegration`
- Admin pages at `/admin` for manufacturers, products, categories, scraper, product-automation, audit log, data actualization
- API routes for `/api/manufacturers`, `/api/products`, `/api/categories`, `/api/attributes`
- Full CRUD for manufacturers, brands, products, categories
- Hierarchical category tree with attributes system
- Product detail editing with images, specs, documents
- Admin layout with full sidebar navigation (Overview, Catalog, Data Pipeline, HearthSync Portal sections)

### Remaining Work
- [ ] Drag-to-reorder sort order on categories
- [ ] Image gallery reorder/set-primary UI enhancement
- [ ] Manufacturer Integration Tracker page (`/admin/manufacturers/[id]/integration`)

---

## Plan 1-B: Scraper Engine & Job Queue ✅ ARCHITECTURE COMPLETE (Vercel-Ready)
*Target: Build the automated data ingestion pipeline per manufacturer*

### What's Done
- **ScraperEngine** (`src/scraper/ScraperEngine.ts`) — Refactored as a **job dispatcher**. Sends jobs to an external worker via HTTP, receives results via callback endpoint, compares/syncs to DB, creates audit logs. Full change detection (add/update/discontinue) implemented.
- **ImagePipeline** (`src/scraper/ImagePipeline.ts`) — Rewritten to upload directly to **Supabase Storage** (in-memory buffer, no local filesystem writes). Vercel-compatible.
- **Queue** (`src/scraper/queue.ts`) — DB-backed job dispatcher (no Redis/BullMQ). Jobs are created as PENDING records and dispatched to the external worker.
- **Cron endpoint** (`/api/cron/process-jobs`) — Vercel Cron-compatible endpoint that polls PENDING jobs and dispatches them. Also checks `OccurrenceSchedule` (HOURLY, DAILY, etc.) to auto-create scheduled jobs.
- **Worker callback** (`/api/scraper/[id]/complete`) — Endpoint for external scraper worker to POST results back. Triggers `ScraperEngine.processResults()`.
- **Workflow chaining** — CATEGORY → PRODUCT_LIST → PRODUCT_PAGE multi-step workflow still works via PENDING job creation.
- `ScraperConfig`, `ScraperJob`, `ScraperWorkflow` Prisma models fully operational.
- Admin scraper page at `/admin/scraper` with config editor, "Run Now" button, job history.
- `vercel.json` configured with cron schedule (every 5 minutes).
- **Removed:** `puppeteer`, `bullmq`, `ioredis` dependencies. `BrandScraper.ts` deleted (moves to external worker).

### What Was Removed (Vercel Deployment)
| Removed | Replaced With |
|---------|--------------|
| `puppeteer` (browser binary) | External scraper worker service (configured via `SCRAPER_WORKER_URL`) |
| `BrandScraper.ts` (Puppeteer class) | External worker handles browser-based scraping |
| `bullmq` + `ioredis` (Redis queue) | DB-backed job queue + Vercel Cron (`/api/cron/process-jobs`) |
| `fs` disk writes (ImagePipeline) | Supabase Storage uploads (in-memory buffer) |
| Puppeteer helpers in `helpers.ts` | Moved to external worker; generic utils (slugify, sanitize, sleep) remain |

### Remaining Work
- [ ] **Set up external scraper worker service** — Separate deployment (Railway, AWS Lambda, or similar) that runs Puppeteer and calls back to `/api/scraper/[id]/complete`
- [ ] Hash deduplication via `fileHash` field on `ProductImage`
- [ ] Scraper health dashboard (`/admin/scraper/health`) with consecutive failure tracking

### Integration Methods Supported
| Method | Implementation | Status |
|--------|---------------|--------|
| **A — Direct API** | Custom per-manufacturer API client | Framework ready (AutomationConfig) |
| **B — Web Scrape** | External worker with Puppeteer (dispatched from Vercel) | Architecture complete, needs worker deploy |
| **C — Distributor Feed** | CSV/EDI import handler (Plan 1-C) | Partially complete |
| **D — Manual** | Admin UI CRUD (Plan 1-A) | ✅ Complete |

